19/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The United States anticipates no problem in next month's presidential elections, according to the US State Department's representative for European issues, Kathleen Stevens. 
During a panel discussion Thursday (18 March) organised by the Voice of America, she added that the international community strongly supports the country in the aftermath of President Boris Trajkovski's death and is ready to help its efforts for Euro-Atlantic integration. 
The other participants on the panel were Macedonian Ambassador to the United States Nikola Dimitrov and the International Crisis Group's former Macedonia project director, Edward Joseph. 
(A1 TV - 17/03/04)
